1. Domain-Specific In-Context Queries
These test if your pipeline pulls relevant context from your 216 vectorized physics and computer science records:

"What algorithm is used to obtain a characterization of the family of sparse graphs?" (Targets Doc 002)

"What does the dark matter field fluid model predict for Mars's rotation?" (Targets Doc 003)

"What are partial cubes and what operations are utilized to construct them?" (Targets Doc 010)

2. Corporate Governance / Refusal Boundaries
These test your strict system prompt constraints ("Answer using ONLY the provided context..."). The pipeline must cleanly refuse to answer these:

"Explain how to design an autonomous drone tracking system using computer vision."

"What are the core differences between a Transformer and a recurrent neural network architecture?"

3. What to Watch for in the Metrics Breakdown:
When you execute these, watch your terminal printouts closely for performance profiling:

Vectorization Time: Should consistently sit under 0.05s to 0.1s (since all-MiniLM is incredibly lightweight).

Retrieval Database Time: Should be rapid (under 0.02s), proving your Weaviate gRPC/HTTP cluster network routing is healthy.

Time to First Token (TTFT): This will show how quickly your Ollama backend on the docker network initializes its context window and begins processing the text stream.